    "paragraphs": [
      {
        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "DTPA does **not have one single binding constant**. Its binding constant depends on the **metal ion**, oxidation state, temperature, ionic strength, and which equilibrium is meant.\n\nIn SRD‑46, DTPA is **ligand_6356 = diethylenetrinitrilopentaacetic acid**, and the core binding equilibrium is usually:\n\n| Equilibrium | SRD-46 beta definition |\n|---|---|\n| \\( \\mathrm{M + L \\rightleftharpoons ML} \\) | **beta_def_812** |\n\nSo the quantity people usually mean is **log β(ML)** for **M + L ⇌ ML**.",
